
To run Hadoop
/usr/local/hadoop/bin/hadoop 

you can check the version

/usr/local/hadoop/bin/hadoop version

Run a query

/usr/local/hadoop/bin/hadoop jar /usr/local/hadoop/share/hadoop/mapreduce/hadoop-mapreduce-examples-3.2.2.jar grep 
~/input ~/outputfolder 'ciao'

It will invoke Hadoop then invoke jar files 

then grep will allow to search in the folder called input

the output will be printed in the 'outputfolder'

the term searched is 'ciao'.
